## Attribution Requirements (Addendum)

In addition to the terms of the Apache License, the following attribution requirements apply:

1. **Credit in Documentation**:
   - All distributed or modified copies of this software must include the following acknowledgment in your documentation or README file:
     ```
     This software includes components developed by The Non Functional Co.
     (https://www.nonfx.com).
     ```

2. **Prominent Display in User Interfaces**:
   - If your product or service includes a user interface, the following attribution must be displayed prominently in an "About" or "Credits" section:
     ```
     Powered by The Non Functional Co. (https://www.nonfx.com)
     ```

3. **Derivative Works Notice**:
   - Any modified or derivative works based on this software must retain the following text in all source files containing significant portions of the original code:
     ```
     This file contains modifications of work originally developed by
     The Non Functional Co. (https://www.nonfx.com).
     ```

4. **Retention of License**:
   - A full copy of this license, including this addendum, must be included in all redistributions or derivative works of the software.

5. **Commercial Licensing**:
   - For revenue-generating uses or commercial distribution of this software, you must obtain a separate commercial license. Contact licensing@thenonfunctional.co for more information.

